# M4 cumulative removal list. The transform unpacks the pristine 0031 blob
# every build, so this list MUST accumulate across slices — a slice-only list
# silently re-adds earlier removals (caught by rootfs-diff on the first
# br-0036 build, 2026-06-06). One NEW slice (≤5 removals) per trial.

# --- slice 1 (br-0035, ADOPTED 2026-06-06, gate 20/20) ---
# telemetry/cloud/phone-home + wsdd2
/usr/sbin/infosvr
/usr/sbin/awsiot
/usr/sbin/mastiff
/usr/bin/asd
/usr/sbin/wsdd2

# --- slice 2 (br-0036, this trial) ---
# networkmap LAN scanner (+ its data dir) and uamsrv (captive-portal
# lighttpd symlink). Live pre-check 2026-06-06: neither running.
/usr/sbin/networkmap
/usr/networkmap
/usr/sbin/uamsrv

# --- slice 3 (br-0037, COMMITTED 2026-06-06; no daily trial cap, trials
# gated only by the dead-man harness — user removed the bogus budget) ---
# AiMesh/cfg ecosystem core daemons; starters nvram-gated (patches 0027-0029)
/usr/sbin/cfg_server
/usr/sbin/wlc_nt
/usr/sbin/lldpd

# --- slice 4 (br-0038) ---
# AiMesh rc-multicall symlinks (all -> rc, none running on br-0037; starters
# re_mode/nvram-gated). The rc binary itself is untouched.
/sbin/amas_lanctrl
/sbin/amas_portstatus
/sbin/amas_ssd_cd
/sbin/conn_diag

# --- slice 5 (br-0039) ---
# band-steer / roaming assist (both off in stock; roamast is an rc symlink)
/usr/sbin/bsd
/sbin/roamast

# --- slice 6 (br-0040) ---
# re_mode-only AiMesh-node crew (all -> rc symlinks; re_mode=0 on this AP,
# none running). Completes br-0033 batch-1 parity except the banned envrams
# wrapper.
/sbin/amas_bhctrl
/sbin/amas_ssd
/sbin/amas_status
/sbin/amas_misc
/sbin/amas_wlcconnect

# --- slice 7 (br-0047) — monitor-retire #1 (Phase-2 rc-drain P2-2) ---
# All four carry RETIRE verdicts in docs/device/plans/plan-phase2-rc-drain.md
# §1.1 (respawn column = "none found" for every one -> safe Pattern-B file
# removal; no watchdog respawn-fail loop). netool/rtkmonitor are /sbin/rc
# MULTICALL SYMLINKS (verified in 0031: "-> rc", 2 bytes) -- deleting the
# symlink removes only that rc entry-point, the /sbin/rc binary is untouched
# (same pattern as slices 4-6). sysstate/wlc_monitor are real /usr/sbin
# binaries (42864 / 9780 B in 0031). wlc_monitor is wifi-ADJACENT by name but
# start_wlc_monitor is a plain monitor with no respawner; the dead-man-guarded
# live kill-test (radios/bridges intact) is owed at TRIAL time before this
# becomes the committed baseline.
/sbin/netool
/sbin/rtkmonitor
/usr/sbin/sysstate
/usr/sbin/wlc_monitor
